HEADWORD: Willsome
<hw>Will"some</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>wilsome</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Willful; obstinate.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fat; indolent.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Doubtful; uncertain.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Will"some*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Willy</ent>⟦br⟧
